{
  "texts": [
    "Park et al.",
    "31 have designed a motion-aided planning mechanism to validate the smooth and collisionfree trajectories for \"high-Degree-Of-Freedom (high-DOF)\" robots that interacted with humans.",
    "Here, the implemented framework utilized the offline learning procedures to recognize human actions with temporal coherence for predicting the actions of humans.",
    "In the developed mechanism, intention-based online planning techniques were employed to learn the essential data to validate the reliable trajectory according to the predicted actions.",
    "Moreover, the Gaussian distribution techniques were utilized to validate the human actions and also validate the probabilities of collision."
  ]
}